% Hand-maintained Rd macro showcase for the multilingual-docs GSoC demo.
% Purpose: exercise every kind of Rd markup, \Sexpr stage/results variant,
% #ifdef/#ifndef conditional, list, table, math, link, and format-conditional
% so we can observe how each one renders (and, later, how each translates).
% Deliberately hand-edited: do NOT regenerate from R/ with roxygen2, that would
% overwrite this file. A literal percent sign must be escaped as \% in Rd.
\name{submit_proposal}
\alias{submit_proposal}
\alias{gsocproposal-macros}
\encoding{UTF-8}
\title{Submit a \gsoc{} Proposal \emph{and} Showcase Rd Macros}
\usage{
submit_proposal()

\method{print}{gsoc_proposal}(x, \dots)
}
\arguments{
\item{x}{An object of class \code{gsoc_proposal}. Dispatches via
  \code{\link{print}}.}
\item{\dots}{Further arguments passed to or from other methods. Argument names
  with special characters (such as \code{\dots}) must round-trip safely.}
}
\description{
Checks whether the current system date falls on or before the package
submission deadline. Returns \code{TRUE} if submissions are still open and
\code{FALSE} once the deadline has passed.

The deadline is not hard-coded in the documentation. It is read from the
package environment \pkgenv{} at \strong{install time}:

Deadline: \Sexpr[results=text,stage=install]{
  as.character(gsocproposal:::.pkg_env$deadline)
}

When you view this help page, the following message is computed \emph{live} at
\strong{render time}:

\Sexpr[results=text,stage=render]{
  dl        <- gsocproposal:::.pkg_env$deadline
  days_left <- as.integer(dl - Sys.Date())
  if (days_left > 0) {
    paste0("The deadline is in ", days_left, " day(s).")
  } else if (days_left == 0) {
    "The deadline is today."
  } else {
    "The deadline has passed, try next year!"
  }
}
}
